# Security

- Treat all external input as untrusted; validate on the server.
- Enforce authorization on the server; never trust client role or owner ID.
- Never hardcode secrets; use env vars; commit `.env.example` only.
- Never log passwords, OTPs, tokens, card data, full bank data or KYC documents.
- Use parameterized queries or the approved ORM.
- Verify webhook signatures; use idempotency for payments and retries.
- Use transactions for financial, booking and inventory/capacity changes.
- Rate-limit OTP and login; expire and rotate sessions.
- File uploads: allowlist type/size, server-side names, private buckets + signed URLs for KYC.
- Require approval for auth model, payment rules and destructive schema changes.
- Add security tests for sensitive flows.
